summary: This document is an email forwarding chat translations related to the Epstein case, noting that FBI marked some chats as responsive but they fall outside the relevant date range for the recipient's investigation.

events.title: Forwarding of Responsive Chats
events.description: An email was sent containing chat translations marked as responsive by the FBI, which were then forwarded to a contractor.

keyFacts: FBI identified and marked certain chat translations as responsive to the investigation.
The responsive chats were provided to a contractor (MI) but fell outside the relevant date range for their inquiry.
The document indicates ongoing investigative work involving chat analysis in September 2020.
